rComments: She is probably one of the few passionate professors I have come across. She genuinely enjoys the subject matter, and you can see it through the way she engages with students. I have taken 3 of her classes and by far one of the gems of the political science department!
Professor Shanks is great at lecturing. She knows how to break down theories and texts so that everyone understands it. If you want an A in this class, be prepared to work for it.

rComments: The course literature was challenging so make time for lots of personal notes. The strength of the course was the professor's ability to relate all the philosophical texts to a wide range of contemporary issues and connect much of the class discussion back to the relevant readings. This resulted in a diverse set of interesting essay topics.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Great Prof honestly knows all her stuff and is very clear and concise, makes lectures enjoyable. Lots of reading but don't worry she breaks down difficult material and makes it clear as day. She's pretty Chill and laid back, few assignments and tests. As long as you do the work you can at least get a B, but have to work a little harder for an A.
